text: Jefferson County is a county located in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 15,709. The county seat is Louisville. The county was created on February 20, 1796 and named for Thomas Jefferson, the third president of the United States. ==References== Category:1796 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
title: Jefferson County, Georgia
